6. Resource monitoring
Build an instance template and deploy a Managed Instance Group (MIG). Set the
Autoscaling policy to trigger at 60% CPU usage (4).
Activity 4: Essential Google Cloud Infrastructure: Core Services
Lab: Resource monitoring
✅ STEP-BY-STEP PROCEDURE
🔹 Step 1: Start Lab & Login
Click Start Lab
Open Google Cloud Console
Login using given:
Username
Password
Accept terms → Skip recovery options
🔹 Step 2: Verify VM Resources
Go to:
👉 Compute Engine → VM Instances
Check these 3 VMs exist:
nginxstack-1
nginxstack-2
nginxstack-3

✅ These will be used for monitoring

🔹 Step 3: Open Cloud Monitoring
Go to:
👉 Navigation Menu → View All Products → Monitoring
Monitoring workspace opens automatically
🔹 Step 4: Create Custom Dashboard
Click Dashboards
Click Create Custom Dashboard
Click New Dashboard
Enter name:
👉 My Dashboard
➤ Add Chart (CPU Utilization)
Click Add Widget
Select Line Chart
Enter:
Title: My Chart
Click Select Metric
Search: CPU utilization

Select:

VM Instance → Instance → CPU utilization
Click Apply
(Optional) Add filter:
Click Add Filter
Explore options
Click Apply

✅ Dashboard created

🔹 Step 5: Use Metrics Explorer (Optional)
Click Metrics Explorer
Try selecting:
Resource: VM Instance
Metric: CPU utilization

👉 Used to analyze metrics without dashboard

🔹 Step 6: Create Alerting Policy
➤ First Condition
Go to Alerting
Click + Create Policy
Click Select Metric

Choose:

VM Instance → CPU usage
Set:
Rolling window: 1 min
Threshold: Above 20
Click Next
➤ Second Condition
Click + Add Condition

Select:

VM Instance → CPU utilization
Set:
Rolling window: 1 min
Threshold: Above 20
Click Next
➤ Multi-condition Rule
Select:
👉 All conditions are met
➤ Add Notification
Click Manage Notification Channels
Add:
Email address
Display name
Save
Go back → Refresh
Select your email
➤ Finalize
Alert Name: My Alert Policy
Click Create Policy

✅ Alert created

🔹 Step 7: Create Resource Group
Go to Monitoring → Groups
Click + Create Group
Enter:
Field	Value
Name	VM instances
Criteria	Contains → nginx
Click Done → Create

✅ Group created (includes all nginx VMs)

🔹 Step 8: Create Uptime Check
Go to Monitoring → Uptime Checks
Click + Create Uptime Check
Enter:
Field	Value
Protocol	HTTP
Resource Type	Instance
Applies To	Group
Group	VM instances
Frequency	1 minute
Click Continue
➤ Add Notification
Select your email notification
➤ Finalize
Title: My Uptime Check
Click Test → Create

✅ Uptime monitoring started

🔹 Step 9: Disable Alert Policy
Go to Monitoring → Alerting
Click See All Policies
Find:
👉 My Alert Policy
Toggle Enabled → OFF
Click Turn Off

✅ Alert disabled

🔹 Step 10: Review

You have successfully:
✔ Created dashboard
✔ Added charts
✔ Created alert with 2 conditions
✔ Created resource group
✔ Configured uptime check
✔ Disabled alert
